<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08040h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08040h">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08040h"> 40(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ (we change opinions)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">J&apos;imagine qu&apos;on nous parle d&apos;un personnage que nous ne connaissons pas encore, et, qu&apos;au cours de la conversation, on nous apprenne qu&apos;il a perdu la vue. Cette information va <mark>modifier brusquement nos appr&eacute;ciations</mark> sur son compte, &agrave; ce point que nous &eacute;prouverons le besoin de revenir sur ce qu&apos;on nous en a dit, afin de corriger nos impressions premi&egrave;res. <br><font color="green">[Let us imagine that someone tells us of a person that we don&apos;t yet know and, in the course of the conversation, we are told that this person has lost his sight. This information will immediately change our view of him to the point that we will have to review what we have been told in order to correct our first impressions.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 301</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
